iterator_traits: provides uniform interface to the properties of an iterator
input_iterator_tag: empty class types used to indicate iterator categories
output_iterator_tag: empty class types used to indicate iterator categories
forward_iterator_tag: empty class types used to indicate iterator categories
bidirectional_iterator_tag: empty class types used to indicate iterator categories
random_access_iterator_tag: empty class types used to indicate iterator categories
iterator: the basic iterator
reverse_iterator: iterator adaptor for reverse-order traversal
move_iterator: iterator adaptor which dereferences to an rvalue reference
back_insert_iterator: iterator adaptor for insertion at the end of a container
front_insert_iterator: iterator adaptor for insertion at the front of a container
insert_iterator: iterator adaptor for insertion into a container
istream_iterator: input iterator that reads from std::basic_istream
ostream_iterator: output iterator that writes to std::basic_ostream
istreambuf_iterator: input iterator that reads from std::basic_streambuf
ostreambuf_iterator: output iterator that writes to std::basic_streambuf
make_move_iterator: creates a std::move_iterator of type inferred from the argument
front_inserter: creates a std::front_insert_iterator of type inferred from the argument
back_inserter: creates a std::back_insert_iterator of type inferred from the argument
inserter: creates a std::insert_iterator of type inferred from the argument
advance: advances an iterator by given distance
distance: returns the distance between two iterators
next: returns increment of an iterator
prev: returns decrement of an iterator
begin: returns an iterator to the beginning of a container or array
cbegin: returns an const iterator to the beginning of a container or array
end: returns an iterator to the end of a container or array
cend: returns an const iterator to the end of a container or array
rbegin: returns a reverse iterator to a container or array
crbegin: returns a const reverse iterator to a container or array
rend: returns a reverse end iterator for a container or array
crend: returns a const reverse end iterator for a container or array
==: check whether 2 iterators are equal
!=: check whether 2 iterators are not equal
<: check whether the left iterator is less than the right one
<=: check whether the left iterator is less or equal than the right one
>: check whether the right iterator is greater than the right one
>=: check whether the left iterator is less or equal than the right one
+: advances the iterator
-: computes the distance between two iterator adaptors
